About this item

Smart summary

Generated by AI

The Caseit Director Padfolio is a sleek, professional writing portfolio made of faux leather. It features a  black leatherette exterior ,  slots for business cards and ID , and  protective document pockets . The portfolio includes a letter-size writing pad and has dimensions of 1.38" depth x 10.16" width x 12.79" height. It also has a  pen and pencil holder , an exterior file and folder pocket, and no binder rings for a clean design. The writing pad is refillable and undated, making it a practical choice for meetings and presentations.

About this item

Product details

The Director by Case•it is a sleek, leatherette padfolio designed for efficient document organization. It features pen holders, card slots, protective pockets, and a letter-size writing pad. The exterior pocket offers easy access to files, making it perfect for meetings, presentations, and conferences. This streamlined portfolio has no binder rings, ensuring a clean design. Dimensions: 1.38" depth x 10.16" width x 12.79" height. New condition. Number of holes: 0
  • Case•it's Sleek and professional Padfolio with a Black leatherette exterior
  • Writing Portfolio
  • Slots for Business Cards and ID
  • Protective document pockets in Binder Portfolio that has no binder rings
  • Holds Letter Size Writing Pad ( 8 1/2 x 11)
  • Wide Rule lined Paper Pad
  • Pen and Pencil Holder
  • Exterior file and folder pocket
  • Undated letter size writing pad is included, and refillable
  • Assembled Product Dimensions 1.38" Depth x 10.16" Width x 12.79 Height.

Excellent!!!

I really like this pad-folio, I took it to my first professional interview on March 19th!! I had 5 copies of my resume, 9 references letters, ID, pen, the pad that is included in which I wrote questions I asked about the unit and position I applied for. There was more than enough room left if was to needed it. Will say one thing the pen compartment while it's spacious it more like for one pen. One pen is all you need, but more will fit, but won't close as good as it does with one slim pen. Has several compartments a big plus. I certainly felt more confident pulling this folio out of my leather tote than I would have a paper/plastic folder. To top it off I got called with an offer an hour later after my interview!!!
